'Successful outcomes' refer to 'PASS' results; 'unsuccessful outcomes' refer to 'FAIL' results. The question seeks a summary of the performance of different test cases across products, providing insight into their reliability. ;
The 'PASS' and 'FAIL' counts for each test case help in assessing the quality of the product being tested. ;
A high 'PASS' count relative to 'FAIL' suggests that the test case is performing well for the product. ;
This data could be used to identify potential areas for improvement in the products by focusing on test cases with higher failure rates.

sql:
SELECT requirement_id 
FROM test_requirements 
WHERE test_id IN (SELECT test_id FROM tests WHERE test_category = 'Radiated Emission');

SELECT DISTINCT t.test_id, t.test_name
FROM tests t
JOIN test_cases tc ON t.test_id = tc.test_case_product_id;

SELECT MIN(test_case_id) 
FROM test_case_results 
WHERE result_id IS NOT NULL AND result_id = 1;
